mbia, in 1889. Her fellow founding trustees included Laura Spelman Rockefeller and suffragist Annie Nathan Meyer, and she remained a Barnard trustee for thirty-two years until her death in 1921."}],"research_tags":[],"artworks":[],"documents":[],"quotes":[],"statues":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"landmarks":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST077","institution_blurb":"Bequeathed $20,000 to Oberlin in her will; husband James funded Talcott Hall women's dormitory in 1887.","relationship":"donor"},{"institution_id":"INST110","relationship":"founder","years":"1889-1921","institution_blurb":"One of eleven charter female trustees who launched the school in 1889; endowed a $100,000 chair in Bible study and served thirty-two years on the board."}],"bio":{"display_name":"Henrietta E Francis Talcott","first_name":"Henrietta","last_name":"Talcott","married_names":["Talcott"],"middle_name":"E","maiden_name":"Francis","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1777579864/Henrietta_Talcott_bir9r8.jpg","photo_notes":"Portrait. Cloudinary."},"research_sources":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"henrietta-francis-1842"},"T01463":{"id":"T01463","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"gender":"male","birth":{"year":1866,"month":9,"day":14,"city":"West Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1944,"month":2,"day":6,"city":"Manhattan","county":"New York","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM112","plot_notes":"Woodlawn Cemetery, Bronx NY. Cypress Plot, Sec 47, Grave 1. GPS: 40.8911853, -73.8694291."},"residence":{"city":"Manhattan","county":"New York","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":true,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"generation_from_john_talcott":8,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1,"descent